{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KN13KxQzTPDh38EUNUPmae","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 4952 tests pass across 182 test files. Zero regressions.\n\n---\n\n## Code Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation\n**Story Status:** verifying\n\n### Issues Found and Fixed\n\n**HIGH (1):**\n- **Telemetry `testResults.coverage` type mismatch** — Validator used `coverage?: number` (optional/undefined) while the canonical `TestResults` type in `agents/types.ts` and `TelemetryEntry` in `telemetry-writer.ts` use `coverage: number | null`. This causes NDJSON entries with inconsistent schemas. Fixed: changed to `coverage: number | null` across `cross-worktree-validator.ts`, `ValidationResult`, `parseTestOutput`, `MergeResult`, and `ConflictResolutionResult`. Updated all test assertions accordingly.\n\n**MEDIUM (3):**\n- **No `maxBuffer` on exec** — Default 1MB buffer could truncate verbose test+coverage output, causing silent data loss and incorrect parsing. Fixed: added `maxBuffer: 10 * 1024 * 1024` (10MB).\n- **`stderr` not captured** — Some test runners (Jest) write failure output to stderr. Losing this means retry context is incomplete. Fixed: combined `stdout + stderr` for both success and error paths.\n- **Did not reuse `TelemetryEntry` type** — Constructed ad-hoc telemetry object instead of importing the canonical type, risking schema drift. Fixed: imported `TelemetryEntry` from `telemetry-writer.ts` and typed the entry.\n\n### Results After Fix\n- All 4952 tests pass (124 in the 3 story files, 182 test files total)\n- Coverage: 96.74% overall, all 180 files above 80% per-file floor\n- Build: clean, no TypeScript errors\n\n### Files Modified\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/cross-worktree-validator.ts` — type fixes, maxBuffer, stderr capture, TelemetryEntry import\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` — `MergeResult.testResults.coverage` type fix\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/merge-agent.ts` — `ConflictResolutionResult.testResults.coverage` type fix\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/cross-worktree-validator.test.ts` — updated assertions for `coverage: null`, maxBuffer\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/merge-agent.test.ts` — updated assertion for `coverage: null`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` — updated assertions for `coverage: null`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation.md` — status changed to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: `coverage` type mismatch (`undefined` vs `null`) across validator, worktree-manager, and merge-agent interfaces. Inconsistent NDJSON telemetry schema.\n- MEDIUM: Missing `maxBuffer` on exec could truncate large test output.\n- MEDIUM: Missing `stderr` capture loses diagnostic info from test runners that write to stderr.\n- MEDIUM: Telemetry object not typed against canonical `TelemetryEntry`, allowing schema drift.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `parseTestOutput` uses first-match regex which could pick up per-suite counts instead of final totals in multi-suite output. Low risk since vitest/jest emit totals last.\n- `writeMergeTelemetry` duplicates the NDJSON write logic (`mkdirSync` + `appendFileSync`) from `telemetry-writer.ts` rather than calling into it. Acceptable because the telemetry-writer's `writeTelemetryEntry` takes a `TaskContext` which is a different shape. Could be refactored to share a lower-level `appendNdjson` helper.\n- Empty `catch` blocks with comment-only suppression are a pattern across the codebase (12+ instances). Acceptable per project convention but a logging adapter would improve debuggability.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None below floor. All files above 80%. Overall 96.74%.\n- No integration test for the full merge-then-validate flow with a real git repo. Unit tests mock `exec` thoroughly but a real git worktree integration test would catch issues with actual test runner output formats.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The validator writes telemetry directly to the filesystem rather than going through the existing `telemetry-writer.ts` module. This creates two independent write paths to the same file. Acceptable for now since both use `appendFileSync` (atomic at the OS level for small writes) and the merge mutex prevents concurrent validator calls.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed and verified.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 30\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 10, Edit: 16, Grep: 6, Glob: 5, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` full suite (~10 lines shown), `npx vitest run 3 files` verbose (~50 lines), `git diff merge-agent.ts` (~80 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 14 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: One glob search for code-review workflow was redundant (searched `.md` then `.yaml`). One grep for `toEqual` patterns was repeated for the same file after partial fixes, but necessary to verify completeness."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a10739f53eb92a46d (use SendMessage with to: 'a10739f53eb92a46d' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 90270\ntool_uses: 78\nduration_ms: 526315</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22206bba-5847-41b1-b510-883e1dd8c0da","uuid":"e13d45fc-a32b-4977-8623-45ea80239f8a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T22:30:03.518Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 