{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DH1XMUHT6mpWRMWYTRCMYn","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 18.3: Cross-Worktree Test Validation\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want the full test suite to run after every merge,\n11\tso that merged code is proven to work before accepting.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a successful clean merge (no conflicts) completes in `mergeWorktree()`, **when** the test suite runs on merged main, **then** all tests must pass for the merge to be accepted — `MergeResult.success` is `true` and `MergeResult.testResults` contains pass/fail counts. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t2. **Given** the test suite fails after a clean merge (no agent resolution involved), **when** failure is detected, **then** the merge is reverted (`git reset --hard HEAD~1`) and `MergeResult` returns `{ success: false, reason: 'tests-failed' }` with the test results — the merge is NOT retried (immediate escalation for clean merges). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t3. **Given** the test suite fails after agent-resolved conflict resolution, **when** failure is detected, **then** the merge is reverted and the agent retries with the test failure output appended as context — up to 3 total attempts (this is the existing `resolveConflicts` retry loop in `merge-agent.ts`). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t4. **Given** a merge completes (clean or agent-resolved) and the test suite passes, **when** the test result is available, **then** test results (passed count, failed count, coverage percentage) are written as a telemetry entry to `.codeharness/telemetry.jsonl` via the telemetry writer. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t5. **Given** the project's workflow defines a test command in `execution.test_command` or defaults to `npm test`, **when** the test suite runs after merge, **then** it uses the configured test command and respects the existing 5-minute timeout from `runTestSuite()`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t6. **Given** `worktree-manager.ts` already runs the test suite after a clean merge and `merge-agent.ts` runs it after agent resolution, **when** this story is complete, **then** a new `src/lib/cross-worktree-validator.ts` module exports a `validateMerge(options: ValidateMergeOptions): Promise<ValidationResult>` function that encapsulates the test-run-after-merge logic, and both `worktree-manager.ts` and `merge-agent.ts` delegate to it instead of having their own `runTestSuite` implementations. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t7. **Given** the `ValidationResult` interface, **when** inspected, **then** it includes: `valid: boolean`, `testResults: { passed: number; failed: number; coverage?: number }`, `output: string` (raw test command stdout for retry context), and `durationMs: number`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t8. **Given** the `ValidateMergeOptions` interface, **when** inspected, **then** it includes: `testCommand: string`, `cwd: string`, `epicId: string`, `storyKey?: string`, and `writeTelemetry: boolean`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t9. **Given** `writeTelemetry` is `true` in `ValidateMergeOptions`, **when** the test suite completes (pass or fail), **then** a telemetry entry is appended to `.codeharness/telemetry.jsonl` with the merge validation results — including `storyKey` set to `merge-{epicId}`, test results, and duration. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t10. **Given** the validator module is wired into both `worktree-manager.ts` and `merge-agent.ts`, **when** the existing test suites for those modules run, **then** all existing tests continue to pass — no regressions. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n36\t\n37\t- [x] Task 1: Create `src/lib/cross-worktree-validator.ts` (AC: #6, #7, #8)\n38\t  - [x] Define `ValidateMergeOptions` interface (testCommand, cwd, epicId, storyKey?, writeTelemetry)\n39\t  - [x] Define `ValidationResult` interface (valid, testResults, output, durationMs)\n40\t  - [x] Extract `runTestSuite` + `parseTestOutput` from worktree-manager.ts into `validateMerge()` function\n41\t  - [x] Export `validateMerge`, `ValidateMergeOptions`, `ValidationResult`\n42\t\n43\t- [x] Task 2: Add telemetry integration (AC: #4, #9)\n44\t  - [x] Import `writeTelemetryEntry` from `telemetry-writer.ts`\n45\t  - [x] When `writeTelemetry: true`, write a TelemetryEntry after test suite completes\n46\t  - [x] Set `storyKey` to `merge-{epicId}`, `epicId` from options, `testResults` from suite run\n47\t  - [x] Write telemetry on both pass and fail outcomes\n48\t\n49\t- [x] Task 3: Refactor `worktree-manager.ts` to use validator (AC: #1, #2, #5, #10)\n50\t  - [x] Replace the private `runTestSuite()` and `parseTestOutput()` methods with a call to `validateMerge()`\n51\t  - [x] Pass `writeTelemetry: true` so merge validation results are logged\n52\t  - [x] Preserve all existing merge behavior (clean merge revert on test failure, cleanup on success)\n53\t  - [x] Run existing worktree-manager tests — all must pass\n54\t\n55\t- [x] Task 4: Refactor `merge-agent.ts` to use validator (AC: #3, #10)\n56\t  - [x] Replace the local `runTestSuite()` and `parseTestOutput()` functions with `validateMerge()`\n57\t  - [x] Pass `writeTelemetry: false` for retry attempts, `true` only for final successful validation\n58\t  - [x] Preserve retry loop behavior: revert on failure, append test output to next attempt prompt\n59\t  - [x] Run existing merge-agent tests — all must pass\n60\t\n61\t- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests for `cross-worktree-validator.ts` (AC: #1-#10)\n62\t  - [x] Test: `validateMerge()` runs test command and returns `valid: true` when tests pass\n63\t  - [x] Test: `validateMerge()` returns `valid: false` with test output when tests fail\n64\t  - [x] Test: `validateMerge()` writes telemetry when `writeTelemetry: true`\n65\t  - [x] Test: `validateMerge()` skips telemetry when `writeTelemetry: false`\n66\t  - [x] Test: `validateMerge()` respects timeout (5 minutes)\n67\t  - [x] Test: `validateMerge()` parses pass/fail/coverage from test output\n68\t  - [x] Test: `ValidateMergeOptions` and `ValidationResult` have correct shapes\n69\t  - [x] Test: telemetry entry has `storyKey: 'merge-{epicId}'` format\n70\t\n71\t## Dev Notes\n72\t\n73\t### Architecture Constraints\n74\t\n75\t- **Architecture Decision 3** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): Cross-worktree test validation runs after every merge. The test suite runs within the merge mutex — the mutex is NOT released between merge and test validation. This prevents another epic from merging while tests are still running on the previous merge.\n76\t- **Merge Safety Pattern**: \"Run the full test suite after merge (not just affected tests). On test failure: revert merge (`git reset --hard HEAD~1`), retry with agent context. On 3 failures: preserve worktree, log escalation, continue with other lanes.\"\n77\t- **Telemetry Write Pattern**: Use append-only NDJSON. Include `version: 1` for forward compat. Write with `appendFileSync`. Never read telemetry during the run.\n78\t\n79\t### What This Story Actually Does\n80\t\n81\tThis story is primarily a **refactoring** story. Both `worktree-manager.ts` and `merge-agent.ts` already have independent `runTestSuite` + `parseTestOutput` implementations. This story:\n82\t\n83\t1. **Extracts** the duplicated test-run logic into a single `cross-worktree-validator.ts` module\n84\t2. **Adds telemetry** — merge validation results are written to the NDJSON telemetry file\n85\t3. **Wires** both existing modules to delegate to the new validator\n86\t\n87\tNo new merge behavior is being added — the test-after-merge logic already exists. The value is deduplication and telemetry.\n88\t\n89\t### Key Files to Create\n90\t\n91\t| File | Why |\n92\t|------|-----|\n93\t| `src/lib/cross-worktree-validator.ts` | New module — extracted test validation + telemetry |\n94\t| `src/lib/__tests__/cross-worktree-validator.test.ts` | Tests for all validator functionality |\n95\t\n96\t### Key Files to Modify\n97\t\n98\t| File | Why |\n99\t|------|-----|\n100\t| `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` | Remove `runTestSuite()` and `parseTestOutput()`, delegate to `validateMerge()` |\n101\t| `src/lib/merge-agent.ts` | Remove `runTestSuite()` and `parseTestOutput()`, delegate to `validateMerge()` |\n102\t| `src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` | Update mocks if needed after refactoring |\n103\t| `src/lib/__tests__/merge-agent.test.ts` | Update mocks if needed after refactoring |\n104\t\n105\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n106\t\n107\t| File | Why |\n108\t|------|-----|\n109\t| `src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts` | `TelemetryEntry`, `writeTelemetryEntry()` — telemetry write interface |\n110\t| `src/lib/agents/types.ts` | `TestResults` type — shape for test result reporting |\n111\t| `src/lib/null-task-registry.ts` | `TaskContext` — context shape if writing telemetry entries |\n112\t\n113\t### Implementation Patterns\n114\t\n115\t**Validator function (extracted from both modules):**\n116\t```typescript\n117\texport async function validateMerge(opts: ValidateMergeOptions): Promise<ValidationResult> {\n118\t  const start = Date.now();\n119\t  try {\n120\t    const { stdout } = await execAsync(opts.testCommand, {\n121\t      cwd: opts.cwd,\n122\t      timeout: 300_000, // 5 minutes\n123\t    });\n124\t    const testResults = parseTestOutput(stdout);\n125\t    const result: ValidationResult = {\n126\t      valid: testResults.failed === 0 && testResults.passed > 0,\n127\t      testResults,\n128\t      output: stdout,\n129\t      durationMs: Date.now() - start,\n130\t    };\n131\t    if (opts.writeTelemetry) {\n132\t      writeMergeTelemetry(opts, result);\n133\t    }\n134\t    return result;\n135\t  } catch (err: unknown) {\n136\t    // Parse output from failed test command\n137\t    // ...same pattern as existing runTestSuite in worktree-manager.ts\n138\t  }\n139\t}\n140\t```\n141\t\n142\t**Telemetry entry for merge validation:**\n143\t```typescript\n144\tfunction writeMergeTelemetry(opts: ValidateMergeOptions, result: ValidationResult): void {\n145\t  const entry: TelemetryEntry = {\n146\t    version: 1,\n147\t    timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n148\t    storyKey: opts.storyKey ?? `merge-${opts.epicId}`,\n149\t    epicId: opts.epicId,\n150\t    duration_ms: result.durationMs,\n151\t    cost_usd: null, // No LLM cost for test validation\n152\t    attempts: null,\n153\t    acResults: null,\n154\t    filesChanged: [],\n155\t    testResults: result.testResults,\n156\t    errors: result.valid ? [] : ['Test suite failed after merge'],\n157\t  };\n158\t  // Use telemetry-writer's appendNdjson function\n159\t}\n160\t```\n161\t\n162\t**Refactoring worktree-manager.ts (conceptual diff):**\n163\t```typescript\n164\t// BEFORE (in mergeWorktree):\n165\tconst testResults = await this.runTestSuite(testCommand);\n166\tif (testResults.failed > 0) { ... }\n167\t\n168\t// AFTER:\n169\tconst validation = await validateMerge({ testCommand, cwd: this.cwd, epicId, writeTelemetry: true });\n170\tif (!validation.valid) { ... }\n171\t```\n172\t\n173\t**Refactoring merge-agent.ts (conceptual diff):**\n174\t```typescript\n175\t// BEFORE (in resolveConflicts loop):\n176\tconst testResults = await runTestSuite(ctx.testCommand, ctx.cwd);\n177\tif (testResults.failed === 0 && testResults.passed > 0) { ... }\n178\t\n179\t// AFTER:\n180\tconst validation = await validateMerge({\n181\t  testCommand: ctx.testCommand,\n182\t  cwd: ctx.cwd,\n183\t  epicId: ctx.epicId,\n184\t  writeTelemetry: attempt === MAX_ATTEMPTS || testResults.valid, // Only on final attempt or success\n185\t});\n186\tif (validation.valid) { ... }\n187\tlastTestFailure = validation.output; // Use raw output for retry context\n188\t```\n189\t\n190\t### Previous Story (18-2) Intelligence\n191\t\n192\t- Story 18-2 created `merge-agent.ts` with its own `runTestSuite()` and `parseTestOutput()` — duplicates of the same functions in `worktree-manager.ts`.\n193\t- The `runTestSuite` in `merge-agent.ts` returns an extra `output: string` field (raw stdout) for retry context. The `worktree-manager.ts` version does not return raw output. The extracted validator must return raw output (the `merge-agent` needs it).\n194\t- Both modules parse test output with identical regex patterns: `/(\\d+)\\s+passed/`, `/(\\d+)\\s+failed/`, `/All files[^|]*\\|\\s*([\\d.]+)/`.\n195\t- The merge-agent tests mock `exec` and `execSync` from `node:child_process`. The worktree-manager tests do the same. After refactoring, tests may need to mock `validateMerge` instead (or continue mocking `exec` and let the validator call through).\n196\t- Module pattern: TypeScript ESM, `.js` import extensions, vitest, vi.mock.\n197\t\n198\t### Edge Cases\n199\t\n200\t- **Test command produces no stdout**: Return `{ passed: 0, failed: 1 }` — same defensive behavior as existing implementations.\n201\t- **Test command times out**: The 5-minute timeout causes an error. Treat as `failed: 1`. Write telemetry with the failure.\n202\t- **Telemetry write fails** (disk full, permission error): Do not let telemetry failure break the validation. Wrap in try/catch, log warning, continue returning the validation result.\n203\t- **Both worktree-manager and merge-agent call validateMerge concurrently**: This should not happen — the merge mutex ensures only one merge at a time. But the validator itself is stateless, so concurrent calls would be safe.\n204\t- **`parseTestOutput` returns 0 passed and 0 failed**: Treat as failure (`valid: false`). A test run that produces no pass/fail output is suspicious.\n205\t\n206\t### Boundary: What This Story Does NOT Include\n207\t\n208\t- **Changing the retry policy** (3 attempts) in merge-agent — that stays as-is.\n209\t- **Adding new merge behaviors** — the merge flow is already complete from 18-1 and 18-2.\n210\t- **Wiring the validator into epic-completion or lane-pool** — those are Epic 19.\n211\t- **TUI display of validation progress** — Epic 20.\n212\t- **Configurable test timeout** — uses the existing 5-minute default.\n213\t\n214\t### Project Structure Notes\n215\t\n216\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n217\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n218\t- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n219\t- Build: `npm run build`, Test: `npm test`\n220\t- The `cross-worktree-validator.ts` should be a focused module (~80-120 lines). The logic is a simple extract-and-add-telemetry.\n221\t- Do NOT duplicate the `parseTestOutput` regex patterns. Extract once, use everywhere.\n222\t\n223\t### References\n224\t\n225\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 18.3]\n226\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 3 -- Merge Serialization & Agent]\n227\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Merge Safety Pattern]\n228\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Telemetry Write Pattern]\n229\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 5 -- Engine-Handled Null Tasks]\n230\t\n231\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n232\t## Verification Requirements\n233\t\n234\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation-proof.md)\n235\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n236\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n237\t\n238\t## Documentation Requirements\n239\t\n240\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n241\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/18-3-cross-worktree-test-validation.md\n242\t\n243\t## Testing Requirements\n244\t\n245\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n246\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n247\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n248\t\n249\t## Dev Agent Record\n250\t\n251\t### Agent Model Used\n252\t\n253\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n254\t\n255\t### Debug Log References\n256\t\n257\t### Completion Notes List\n258\t\n259\t- Extracted duplicated `runTestSuite()` and `parseTestOutput()` from `worktree-manager.ts` and `merge-agent.ts` into `cross-worktree-validator.ts`\n260\t- Added NDJSON telemetry writes for merge validation results\n261\t- `writeMergeTelemetry` exported so merge-agent can defer telemetry to success/final-attempt\n262\t- All 124 tests pass (33 new + 66 worktree-manager + 25 merge-agent), zero regressions\n263\t- 100% statement/line/function coverage on cross-worktree-validator.ts\n264\t\n265\t### File List\n266\t\n267\t- `src/lib/cross-worktree-validator.ts` (created)\n268\t- `src/lib/__tests__/cross-worktree-validator.test.ts` (created)\n269\t- `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` (modified — removed runTestSuite/parseTestOutput, delegates to validateMerge)\n270\t- `src/lib/merge-agent.ts` (modified — removed runTestSuite/parseTestOutput, delegates to validateMerge)\n271\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DyuE8H75hShivUjUvnNUNi","session_id":"22206bba-5847-41b1-b510-883e1dd8c0da","uuid":"25f5b57f-12d3-4335-861a-dae19ff22c7d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T22:30:47.761Z"}
